//but it all boils down to the fact that the nth passenger has only two options i.e nth seat and the remaining random seat
// so the prob is 1/2 for n>=2 as for n=1 theres only person so he will obviously seat in his assigned seat.
//essentially f(n) = 1 / n + (n - 2) / n * f(n - 1)

